## ENGINEERING IMPROVEMENTS TO DATE (as of 2026-04-28)
- Removed hardcoded Supabase key from Python/batch flow; env loading now handled through `main.py`.
- Hardened DB connection layer with session reuse, retry, and backoff.
- Added regression tests for prior detector failures.
- Cleaned historical duplicate flags once in Supabase.
- Moved dashboard flag review away from direct anonymous table updates.
- Added Nagpur support across scraper, geocode, dashboard, and city flow.
- Improved 99acres scraper for larger cities and switched buy/sale scraping to resale route.
- Improved 99acres area unit handling: sqft, sq-yard, sqm.
- Improved locality normalization and alias handling.
- Fixed sq-yard area issue so huge sq-yard listings no longer produce tiny sqft values.
- Added confidence scoring logic for `locality_price_spike`.
- Increased `listing_price_outlier` minimum comparable group size from 4 to 6.
- Updated `locality_price_spike` dedupe so reviewed/closed flags do not keep returning every run.
- Confirmed Supabase disk size is not currently a problem.

